net.trajano.jetng.apt

Annotation Type Emit


  • public @interface Emit
    Code emitter. Annotated classes must have one constructor that takes in an element.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      String processorName
      Name of the processor class that will be generated.
      String[] supportedAnnotationTypes
      Supported annotation types.
      String template
      JET template class.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String packageName
      Package name where the generator class will reside, if it is not specified, then the package name of the class annotated will be used.
      String qualifiedNameMethod
      Method name found in the annotated class used to get the qualified name of the written class.
      SourceVersion supportedSourceVersion
      Supported source version.

    • Element Detail

      • processorName

        public abstract String processorName
        Name of the processor class that will be generated.
        Returns:

      • supportedAnnotationTypes

        public abstract String[] supportedAnnotationTypes
        Supported annotation types. This is a String[] as APT cannot access the class itself.
        Returns:

      • template

        public abstract String template
        JET template class. This is a String as APT cannot access the class itself.
        Returns:

      • qualifiedNameMethod

        public abstract String qualifiedNameMethod
        Method name found in the annotated class used to get the qualified name of the written class.
        Returns:
        Default:
        "getQualifiedName"

      • supportedSourceVersion

        public abstract SourceVersion supportedSourceVersion
        Supported source version.
        Returns:
        Default:
        javax.lang.model.SourceVersion.RELEASE_6
